The paper deals with the design and maintenance of a robust overlay network, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The network is designed to tolerate adversarial churn, which is a common concern in network security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the efficient maintenance of the overlay structure, which involves addressing and routing messages, a topic in computer networks (cs.NI). The committees formed in the network are stable and capable of performing sustained computation, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the network, which could fall under the category of social networks or online communities (cs.SI).
